"""
.gitignore

PURPOSE:
  This file tells Git which files and directories to IGNORE when committing
  to version control. Files listed here will NOT be uploaded to GitHub/GitLab.

WHY THIS MATTERS:
  - Prevents sensitive data from being exposed publicly
  - Avoids committing large generated files (databases, cache)
  - Keeps repository clean and focused on source code

IMPORTANT: SECRET FILES SECTION
  DO NOT COMMIT FILES CONTAINING CREDENTIALS, KEYS, OR SECRETS!

  Files that MUST be ignored:
  ✓ .env - Contains OpenAI API keys and other sensitive configuration
  ✓ credentials.json - Service account keys
  ✓ *.key, *.pem - Private cryptographic keys
  ✓ secrets/ - Folder with any secrets
  ✓ .aws, .gcp - Cloud provider credentials

  If you accidentally commit secrets, IMMEDIATELY revoke them!

MAINTENANCE:
  - Review this file whenever adding new dependencies or tools
  - Add new patterns as needed for your workflow
  - Never use .gitignore to hide bugs or broken code
"""

# ============================================================================
# CRITICAL: SECRET FILES - NEVER COMMIT THESE
# ============================================================================
# OpenAI API key and environment variables
.env
.env.local
.env.*.local

# Credentials and keys
credentials.json
*.key
*.pem
secrets/
.aws/
.gcp/

# ============================================================================
# PYTHON: VIRTUAL ENVIRONMENT AND CACHE
# ============================================================================
# Virtual environment directory (contains local package installations)
.venv/
venv/
env/

# Python compiled bytecode and cache
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
*$py.class
*.so

# ============================================================================
# DATABASE AND LARGE FILES
# ============================================================================
# ChromaDB vector stores (large, generated at runtime, not source code)
chroma_db/
chroma_db_test/

# Python package cache
*.egg-info/
dist/
build/

# ============================================================================
# IDE AND EDITOR SETTINGS
# ============================================================================
# VS Code
.vscode/

# PyCharm
.idea/
*.swp
*.swo

# ============================================================================
# GENERATED FILES
# ============================================================================
# Analysis outputs (can be regenerated by running pipelines)
strategic_analysis_output*.md

# OS files
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db

# ============================================================================
# WINDOWS DEVICE FILES
# ============================================================================
# Windows reserved device name - should never be tracked
# This is created when subprocess output is misdirected to Windows null device
nul
NUL

# ============================================================================
# GENERATED OUTPUT AND TEMPORARY FILES
# ============================================================================
# Generated reports and analysis outputs
outputs/
archived_reports/

# Temporary files
*.tmp
*.temp